  "instructions": [
    "Combine chicken necks, carrots, celery, onion, and garlic in a large stockpot.",
    "Pour in chicken stock and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a simmer.",
    "Let cook for 30 minutes, or until the chicken is tender.",
    "Strain the broth through a fine-mesh sieve into a large bowl.",
    "Add heavy cream and stir to combine.",
    "Return the broth to the pot and add parsley, dill, salt, and pepper.",
    "Simmer for an additional 10-15 minutes, or until heated through.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
